President Trump presented the Presidential Medal of Freedom to baseball legend Mariano Rivera in a ceremony at the White House. Rivera, who played for the New York Yankees, is considered one of the greatest pitchers of all time. He was praised for his dominance on the mound and his contributions to American sports and society. Rivera, who is known for his humility and deep Christian faith, thanked his family and expressed his gratitude for being able to achieve the American Dream. The ceremony highlighted Rivera's achievements, including his World Series victories and his record-breaking number of saves. He was also recognized for his philanthropic efforts through the Mariano Rivera Foundation.